France Aims to Contain Budget Deficit to 0.8
PARIS , December 23 ( Xinhua ) -- France is aiming to reduce its budget deficit to from 0.8 to 1.2 percent of the gross domestic product ( GDP ) by the year 2002 , said the Ministry of Finance on Wednesday .
The government bases the hypothesis on the perspectives of an average annual growth of from 2.5 to 3 percent from 2000 to 2002 , while the volume of public spendings is expected to grow by 1 percent each year in the next three years .
The public debt should be reduced to from 55.6 to 57.6 percent of the GDP by the year 2002 , as is compared with 58.2 percent in 1998 .
Taxes and social contributions by enterprises and individuals will stand at around 45 percent of the GDP .
The French government will submit the plural-annual program to the European Union in Brussels for approval .
